PositiveReal a = 10
Real aa = 10

Real b ~ LogNormal(logMean=0.0, logSd=1.0) observed as a
Real c ~ LogNormal(logMean=0.0, logSd=1.0) observed between [a + b, 100]
Real d ~ LogNormal(logMean=0.0, logSd=1.0) observed as "Hallo"

Real e[i] ~ LogNormal(logMean=1.0*i, logSd=1.0) observed as i for i in 1:10
Real f[i, j] ~ LogNormal(logMean=1.0*i, logSd=1.0) observed as aa for i in 1:10 for j in 1:2

// EXPECT AST
// (AS PositiveReal a 10)
// (AS Real aa 10)
// (OA (DR Real b (CA LogNormal (AA logMean 0.0) (AA logSd 1.0))) a)
// (OB (DR Real c (CA LogNormal (AA logMean 0.0) (AA logSd 1.0))) (+ a b) 100)
// (OA (DR Real d (CA LogNormal (AA logMean 0.0) (AA logSd 1.0))) "Hallo")
// (IS (OA (DR Real e (CA LogNormal (AA logMean (* 1.0 i)) (AA logSd 1.0))) i) i (R 1 10))
// (IS (OA (DR Real f (CA LogNormal (AA logMean (* 1.0 i)) (AA logSd 1.0))) aa) i (R 1 10) j (R 1 2))
// EXPECT AST

// EXPECT TYPE_ERRORS
// Wrong observation type. You specify an observation of type 'Real' for a random variable of type 'PositiveReal'. Use an observation of type 'PositiveReal' instead.
// Wrong observation type. You specify an observation of type 'String' for a random variable of type 'PositiveReal'. Use an observation of type 'PositiveReal' instead.
// Wrong observation type. You specify an observation of type 'Real' for a random variable of type 'PositiveReal'. Use an observation of type 'PositiveReal' instead.
// EXPECT TYPE_ERRORS
